# Project 2 - Iris Classification using K-Nearest Neighbors (KNN)

## Overview

This project is developed as part of the Artificial Intelligence Internship at DecodeLabs.

The main objective of this project is to build a Machine Learning classification model using the famous Iris dataset and the K-Nearest Neighbors (KNN) algorithm.

The model learns patterns from flower measurements and predicts the correct flower species based on the input data.

